            "answer_text": "It's okay with sucking all the oxygen out of the room. It wants to frame police brutality as a \u2018black' issue when every color American experiences it. The killings at the hands of US police no one is talking about Yes black ID'd experience it a notch up but it's not presented that way. That would require somewhat more attention not all of it. Dark skin matters would be more accurate. People considered black won't experience that same social friction because can have tan or peach skin. A dark skinned South Asian or Polynesian can have a \u201cblack\u201d experience. Unproductive. Okay, those who haven't acknowledged a bias aren't at this point so now what? It started strong and has fizzled but being kept on life support. Turning it into blackvotingmatters would actually be productive. I've seen he hash tag used when a black ID'd person has been killed by the police with no clear information. It can be justified sometimes so it comes off like tribalism and defending a criminal. Snap assumptions either way is wrong. Splintered. Anyone and everyone uses it. Its decentralized but comes off as a singular voice when it's factions. ",
